<CSSPerspective-origin>
<summary>
The <strong><c>perspective-origin</c></strong> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS">CSS</see> property determines the position at which the viewer is looking. It is used as the <strong>vanishing point</strong> by the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/perspective">perspective</see> property.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>EmbedInteractiveExample("pages/css/perspective-origin.html")</para><para>The <strong><c>perspective-origin</c></strong> and <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/'perspective'">'perspective'</see> properties are attached to the parent of a child transformed in 3-dimensional space, unlike the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transform-function/perspective"><c>perspective()</c></see> transform function which is placed on the element being transformed.</para>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_transforms/Using_CSS_transforms">Using CSS Transforms</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/'transform-style'">'transform-style'</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/'transform-function'">'transform-function'</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/'perspective'">'perspective'</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/transform-function/perspective"><c>transform: perspective()</c></see> function<br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/perspective-origin"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
</CSSPerspective-origin>
